parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or stiff
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes a longer time to stop
the ABS light comes on
the vehicle slides or skids when braking
the brakes lock up
and the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause loss of braking power, extended stopping distances, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR valve can cause the engine to stall or idle rough, leading to potential accidents or fires.
symptoms: The engine stalls or idles rough
the vehicle won't start
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle dies out while driving
smoke comes from the floor area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause serious damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants.
symptoms: Engine catches on fire
fire is contained to the engine compartment
fire extinguishes itself.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel injector leaks can cause the engine to idle rough, leading to potential accidents or fires.
symptoms: The engine idles rough
fuel fumes are smelled
the vehicle almost cuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the vehicle dies out while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to service the ABS system can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Uncertainty about whether the ABS system has been serviced
concern about the safety of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failures can cause stalling, difficulty starting the vehicle, and in extreme cases, fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling
difficulty starting the vehicle
fuel leaks
fuel being injected back into the engine
strong gas smell
flames coming from the rear of the vehicle near the fuel tank.
